---
import ToolLayout from "../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro";

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is the character limit for a Discord server name?",
    answer:
      "Discord server names can be between 2 and 100 characters long. However, keeping them under 30 characters is recommended so they display fully without cropping on the sidebar.",
  },
  {
    question:
      "Can I use special symbols and custom fonts in Discord server names?",
    answer:
      "Yes, Discord supports standard Unicode symbols (like ✧, ✦, 🪐, 🎮) and special math/alphanumeric font styles in server names. Our tool formats these automatically.",
  },
  {
    question: "Are emojis allowed in a Discord server name?",
    answer:
      "Yes, you can include standard emojis in a server name. They are a great way to add visual identity to your server header listing.",
  },
  {
    question: "How do I change the name of my Discord server?",
    answer:
      "To change your server name, open your server on Discord, click the server name header to open the dropdown menu, select 'Server Settings', modify the 'Server Name' field, and click 'Save Changes'.",
  },
  {
    question: "Will changing my Discord server name break invite links?",
    answer:
      "No, changing the name of your server will not break or alter any existing active server invite links. The server ID remains the same.",
  },
];
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Discord Server Name Generator - Cool & Aesthetic Ideas"
  description="Generate cool, aesthetic, and unique server name ideas for Discord. Customize server names by gaming, social, study, and anime niches."
  toolName="Discord Server Name Generator"
  toolDescription="Create unique, eye-catching Discord server names. Customize by niche tones, toggle aesthetic decorations, and preview on a server list sidebar."
  category="Writing Tools"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <div slot="calculator" class="calc-card glass">
    <!-- Main Advanced Grid Layout -->
    <div class="calc-grid">
      <!-- Left Column: Generator Inputs -->
      <div class="calc-form-column">
        <div class="calc-form">
          <!-- Seed Name Input -->
          <div class="form-group">
            <label for="seed-input" class="icon-label">
              <svg
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                stroke="currentColor"
                class="field-icon"
              >
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M15.75 5.25a3 3 0 0 1 3 3m3 0a6 6 0 0 1-7.029 5.912c-.563-.097-1.159.026-1.563.43L10.5 17.25H8.25v2.25H6v2.25H2.25v-2.818c0-.597.237-1.17.659-1.591l6.499-6.499c.404-.404.527-1 .43-1.563A6 6 0 1 1 21.75 8.25Z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
              Seed Keyword / Topic
            </label>
            <input
              type="text"
              id="seed-input"
              class="form-input"
              placeholder="e.g. lounge, nexus, guild"
              value="lounge"
            />
          </div>

          <div
            style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem;"
          >
            <!-- Server Niche Style -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="niche-select" class="icon-label">Server Niche</label>
              <select
                id="niche-select"
                class="form-input"
                style="height: 48px; background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 0 12px; color: var(--color-text);"
              >
                <option value="gaming">Gaming / Clan</option>
                <option value="community">Community / Social</option>
                <option value="aesthetic">Aesthetic / Chill</option>
                <option value="anime">Anime / Otaku</option>
                <option value="study">Study / Professional</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <!-- Formatting Dropdown -->
            <div class="form-group">
              <label for="format-select" class="icon-label"
                >Format Preference</label
              >
              <select
                id="format-select"
                class="form-input"
                style="height: 48px; background: var(--color-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 0 12px; color: var(--color-text);"
              >
                <option value="symbols">Aesthetic Symbols (✧, ✦)</option>
                <option value="clean">Clean (Text Only)</option>
                <option value="spaces">Space Separated (L o u n g e)</option>
                <option value="font">Special Font Styles (𝔘𝔫𝔦𝔠𝔬𝔡𝔢)</option>
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Actions -->
          <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="button" id="generate-btn" class="calc-btn"
              >Generate Server Names</button
            >
            <button type="button" id="reset-btn" class="calc-btn-secondary"
              >Reset Inputs</button
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right Column: Live Mockup Card -->
      <div class="calc-editor-column">
        <!-- Live Discord Server List Mockup Preview -->
        <div
          class="discord-server-preview glass"
          style="background: #2f3136; color: #ffffff; border-radius: 16px; overflow: hidden; max-width: 320px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%; border: 1px solid #202225; text-align: left; box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); display: flex; height: 260px;"
        >
          <!-- Server Left Icon Sidebar (Standard Discord Style) -->
          <div
            style="background: #202225; width: 64px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 8px; padding-top: 12px; flex-shrink: 0;"
          >
            <!-- Server Icon Circle -->
            <div
              id="mockup-server-bubble"
              style="width: 44px; height: 44px; border-radius: 50%; background: #5865f2; color: #ffffff; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 800; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s;"
              title="Creators Feel Server"
            >
              CF
            </div>

            <div
              style="width: 30px; height: 2px; background: #2f3136; border-radius: 1px;"
            >
            </div>

            <!-- Dummy Server bubbles -->
            <div
              style="width: 44px; height: 44px; border-radius: 50%; background: #2f3136; color: #8e9297; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700;"
            >
              G1
            </div>
            <div
              style="width: 44px; height: 44px; border-radius: 50%; background: #2f3136; color: #8e9297; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700;"
            >
              G2
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Channel List Area -->
          <div
            style="flex-grow: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; background: #2f3136; min-width: 0;"
          >
            <!-- Header (Server Name) -->
            <div
              style="height: 48px; border-bottom: 1px solid #202225; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; padding: 0 1rem; flex-shrink: 0; box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.2); min-width: 0;"
            >
              <span
                id="mockup-server-name"
                style="font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 800; color: #ffffff; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; white-space: nowrap; padding-right: 4px;"
                >✦ lounge ✦</span
              >
              <svg
                style="width: 18px; height: 18px; color: #b9bbbe; flex-shrink: 0;"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                fill="none"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
                ><path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5"></path></svg
              >
            </div>

            <!-- Channels Listing -->
            <div
              style="padding: 1rem 0.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; overflow-y: auto; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #8e9297;"
            >
              <!-- Welcome -->
              <div
                style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 6px 8px; border-radius: 4px; background: #34373c; color: #ffffff; cursor: pointer;"
              >
                <span>#</span>
                <span>welcome-rules</span>
              </div>
              <!-- General -->
              <div
                style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 6px 8px; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer;"
              >
                <span>#</span>
                <span>general-chat</span>
              </div>
              <!-- Gaming -->
              <div
                style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 6px 8px; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer;"
              >
                <span>#</span>
                <span>gaming-zone</span>
              </div>
              <!-- Voice -->
              <div
                style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; padding: 6px 8px; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer;"
              >
                <span>🔊</span>
                <span>Voice Lounge</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Generated Results Section -->
    <div
      id="results-wrapper"
      class="hidden"
      style="margin-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px dashed var(--color-border); padding-top: 1.5rem;"
    >
      <h3
        style="font-size: 1.05rem; font-weight: 800; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0 0 1rem 0; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;"
      >
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          fill="none"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          stroke-width="1.5"
          stroke="currentColor"
          style="width: 20px; height: 20px; color: var(--color-brand);"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            d="M9 12.75 11.25 15 15 9.75M21 12c0 1.268-.63 2.39-1.593 3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043 3.296 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-3.296 1.043A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 12 21c-1.268 0-2.39-.63-3.068-1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1-3.296-1.043 3.745 3.745 0 0 1-1.043-3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 3 12c0-1.268.63-2.39 1.593-3.068a3.745 3.745 0 0 1 1.043-3.296 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296-1.043A3.746 3.746 0 0 1 12 3c1.268 0 2.39.63 3.068 1.593a3.746 3.746 0 0 1 3.296 1.043 3.746 3.746 0 0 1 1.043 3.296A3.745 3.745 0 0 1 21 12Z"
          ></path>
        </svg>
        Suggested Discord Server Names
      </h3>

      <div class="usernames-grid" id="generated-servers-container">
        <!-- Results dynamic content goes here -->
      </div>

      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        <button
          type="button"
          id="generate-more-btn"
          class="calc-btn"
          style="max-width: 200px; padding: 0 1.5rem;">Generate More</button
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div slot="about" class="editorial-content">
    <h2>Discord Server Name Generator: Build Cool Server Identities</h2>
    <div
      style="margin: 1.5rem 0; background: var(--color-bg-alt); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid var(--color-brand);"
    >
      <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        🦋 <strong
          >Looking to audit bio templates or write custom profile layouts?</strong
        > Try our free <a
          href="/tools/discord-bio-generator"
          style="color: var(--color-brand); text-decoration: underline;"
          >Discord Bio Generator</a
        > to customize your 'About Me' text box inside the strict 190-character ceiling.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>
      Creating a successful Discord server starts with building a distinct
      brand. In a listing of hundreds of public servers, your server name is the
      first element potential members notice. A poorly formatted or generic name
      will fail to attract users, while a highly stylized name with aesthetic
      symbols catches their attention. Whether you are running a gaming clan, an
      anime fan club, a professional study group, or a friendly chat lounge, our
      free <strong>discord server name generator</strong> helps you discover unique
      name variations that make your server stand out.
    </p>

    <h3>How to Use This Tool</h3>
    <p>
      To generate and preview cool Discord server names, follow these simple
      directions:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <strong>Seed Topic:</strong> Enter a base keyword or server theme (e.g. lounge,
        nexus, cafe).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Niche Select:</strong> Pick a style tone matching your community (Gaming,
        Social, Aesthetic, Anime, or Study).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Format Select:</strong> Choose a separator formatting (Aesthetic symbols,
        Clean text, spaces, or custom unicode fonts).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Generate Names:</strong> Click **Generate Server Names** to construct
        15 unique ideas.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Preview & Copy:</strong> Click any generated name to preview it in
        the Discord server list mockup, and copy it with the pill-shaped button. Click
        **Generate More** to append 5 more options.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h3>What is Discord Server</h3>
    <p>
      A Discord server is a dedicated online space where people can communicate,
      collaborate, and build communities around shared interests. Think of it as
      a virtual clubhouse that contains multiple text and voice channels, each
      organized for different topics or activities.
    </p>
    <p>
      For example, a gaming server might have separate channels for
      announcements, strategy discussions, voice chat, memes, and support.
      Server owners can customize permissions, create roles for moderators and
      members, and automate tasks using bots. Discord servers are widely used by
      content creators, businesses, educators, developers, gaming communities,
      and hobby groups because they make it easy to keep conversations organized
      while supporting thousands of members.
    </p>
    <p>
      Members can join public servers through invite links or participate in
      private servers that require approval. Features such as screen sharing,
      file sharing, events, polls, and voice or video calls help communities
      stay active and engaged. Whether you're managing a small team or building
      a large online audience, a Discord server provides a flexible and scalable
      way to connect people in real time.
    </p>
    <p>
      By organizing discussions into dedicated channels and assigning
      appropriate roles, server owners can create a welcoming environment that
      encourages meaningful conversations, collaboration, and long-term
      community growth.
    </p>

    <h3>How Does It Work?</h3>
    <p>
      Our <strong>discord name generator</strong> processes input keywords using custom
      naming algorithms:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Style Matching:</strong> Maps specific prefixes and suffixes related
        to your niche (e.g. adding `.gg/` or `🎮` for gaming, and `✦`, `✧`, or `✿`
        for aesthetic chill zones).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Font Stylization:</strong> Converts standard letters into decorative
        Unicode letters (like gothic, double-struck, or cursive characters).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Character Checks:</strong> Verifies names fit within the 100-character
        ceiling and formats them for sidebar readability.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Example Calculation</h3>
    <p>Let's look at how an aesthetic server name is compiled:</p>
    <p>
      <strong>Input Seed Name:</strong> `"Haven"`<br />
      <strong>Server Niche selected:</strong> `"Aesthetic / Chill"`<br />
      <strong>Format selected:</strong> `"With Aesthetic Symbols"`
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Calculation Process:</strong><br />
      ✦ Base name: `"Haven"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>5 characters</strong>.<br />
      ✦ Niche suffix: `"Cafe"` $\rightarrow$ <strong>4 characters</strong>.<br
      />
      ✦ Aesthetic symbols: `"✦"` (prefix) and `"✦"` (suffix) $\rightarrow$ <strong
        >4 characters</strong
      > (with spaces).<br />
      ✦ Combined output: `"✦ Haven Cafe ✦"` $\rightarrow$ <strong
        >14 characters</strong
      >.<br />
      ✦ Character limit check: `14 < 300 characters`.
    </p>
    <p>
      The generated server name is `✦ Haven Cafe ✦`. It complies with Discord's
      rules.
    </p>

    <h3>Features</h3>
    <p>
      This <strong>free discord server name generator</strong> includes:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Live Server List Mockup:</strong> Review how your server name displays
        in the Discord server header banner and circular sidebar bubble.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Generate More Options:</strong> Append 5 more unique server name variations
        on click.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Multiple Niche Tones:</strong> Tailored prefixes and suffixes for
        esports clans, fan clubs, cozy cafes, and study groups.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Pill-Shaped Tactile Copy Buttons:</strong> Instantly copy your favorite
        server name with a single click.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Who Should Use This Tool?</h3>
    <p>This generator is designed for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Esports Teams & Clan Leaders:</strong> Creating cool names for team
        servers (e.g. `Vortex Esports | Recruitment`).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Aesthetic Community Owners:</strong> Designing soft, cozy, and aesthetic
        server themes (e.g. `✦ cozy tea lounge ✦`).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Anime Fan Clubs:</strong> Exploring Japanese or Otaku-themed name
        variations (e.g. `Akihabara | Anime Nexus 🪐`).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Study Group Moderators:</strong> Building clean, professional study
        grids (e.g. `Computer Science Study Hub 📚`).
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

